\begin_layout Standard
Note that this subgroup is isomorphic to 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{8}$
\end_inset

 by labeling the matrices in the first row as 
\begin_inset Formula $1,i,j,k$
\end_inset

.
 There are four 
\begin_inset Formula $3$
\end_inset

-Sylow subgroups:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\align center
\begin_inset Tabular
<lyxtabular version="3" rows="1" columns="4">
