\backslash
label{defn}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

 be a group and let 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 be a 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

-module.
 We define the 
\series bold
cohomology group of 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

 with coefficients in 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 
\series default
by
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathrm{H}(G,A):=\mathrm{Ext}_{\mathbb{Z}[G]}(\mathbb{Z},A).
\]

\end_inset

We can explicitely compute 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathrm{H}(G,A)$
\end_inset

 using the fact that 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{Z}[[G]]$
\end_inset

 is a free resolutions of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{Z}$
\end_inset

 over 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{Z}[G]$
\end_inset

.
 Namely
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathrm{H}(G,A)=\mathrm{H}(\mathrm{Hom}_{\mathbb{Z}[G]}^{\star}(\mathbb{Z}[[G]],A)).
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{defn}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

