\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{rem}
\backslash
label{rem}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $(E,\alpha,\beta)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $(E,\alpha',\beta')$
\end_inset

 be extensions of 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

 by 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

.
 If 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi\colon(E,\alpha,\beta)\to(E,\alpha',\beta')$
\end_inset

 is an isomorphism of extensions, then it induces an isomorphism 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi\colon E\to E'$
\end_inset

 of groups.
 On the other hand, if 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi\colon E\to E'$
\end_inset

 is an isomorphism of extensions, then it does not necessarily give rise
 to an isomorphism between the extensions 
\begin_inset Formula $(E,\alpha,\beta)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $(E,\alpha',\beta')$
\end_inset

.
 Indeed, we need 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi$
\end_inset

 to satisfy extra constraints, namely 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha\varphi=\alpha'$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta'\varphi=\beta$
\end_inset

.
 However, 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi$
\end_inset

 does give rise to an isomorphism of extensions between 
\begin_inset Formula $(E,\alpha,\beta)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $(E,\varphi\alpha,\pi\varphi^{-1})$
\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{rem}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{prop}
\backslash
label{prop}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $(E,\alpha,\beta)$
\end_inset

 be an extension of 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

 by 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

.
 Then we have a bijection of isomorphism classes
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
[E,\alpha,\beta]\cong[E]
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{prop}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{proof}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 The first thing we need to do is to translate the short exact sequence
 
