\begin_layout Standard
where 
\begin_inset Formula $\iota$
\end_inset

 is the inclusion map and 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi$
\end_inset

 is the is the quotient map.
 Define a map 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma\colon G\to E\slash\alpha(A)$
\end_inset

 as follows: for each 
\begin_inset Formula $g\in G$
\end_inset

 choose a lift 
\begin_inset Formula $e_{g}\in E$
\end_inset

