\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

An extension 
\begin_inset Formula $E'$
\end_inset

 of 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

 by 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 is said to be 
\begin_inset Formula $\textbf{isomorphic}$
\end_inset

 to 
\begin_inset Formula $E$
\end_inset

 if there exists an isomorphism 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi:E\to E'$
\end_inset

 such that the following diagram is commutative
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
