\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
is a short exact sequence.
 It turns out that a short exact sequence like 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

(
\backslash
ref{d1})
\end_layout

\end_inset

 is isomorphic to a short exact sequence like 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

(
\backslash
ref{d2})
\end_layout

\end_inset

 in the following way:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{center} 
\backslash
