\begin_layout Standard
From universality of 
\begin_inset Formula $(T,b)$
\end_inset

, a unique linear map 
\begin_inset Formula $T\to T$
\end_inset

 fits in 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

(
\backslash
ref{tensoruniqueuptouniqueiso3})
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
 The identity map works, so 
\begin_inset Formula $f'\circ f=1_{T}$
\end_inset

.
 Similarly, 
\begin_inset Formula $f\circ f'=1_{T'}$
\end_inset

 by stacking 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

(
\backslash
ref{tensoruniqueuptouniqueiso1})
\end_layout

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

(
\backslash
ref{tensoruniqueuptouniqueiso2})
\end_layout

\end_inset

 in the other order.
 Thus 
\begin_inset Formula $T$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $T'$
\end_inset

 are isomorphic 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-modules by 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 and also 
\begin_inset Formula $f\circ b=f'$
\end_inset

, which means 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 identifies 
\begin_inset Formula $b$
\end_inset

 with 
\begin_inset Formula $b'$
\end_inset

.
 So two tensor products of 
\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 can be identified with each other in a unique way compatible with the distingui
shed bilinear maps to them from 
\begin_inset Formula $M\times N$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Construction of Tensor Product
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{theorem}
\backslash
label{theorem}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 A tensor product of 
\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 exists.
 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{theorem}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{proof}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Consider 
\begin_inset Formula $M\times N$
\end_inset

 simply as a set.
 We form the free 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-module on this set:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
F_{R}(M\times N)=\bigoplus_{(u,v)\in M\times N}R\delta_{(u,v)}.
\]

\end_inset

Let 
\begin_inset Formula $D$
\end_inset

 be the submodule of 
\begin_inset Formula $F_{R}(M\times N)$
\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{proof}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
The Covariant Functor 
\begin_inset Formula $-\otimes_{R}N$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{prop}
\backslash
label{prop}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 be an 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-module.
 We obtain a covariant functor
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
-\otimes_{R}N\colon\mathbf{Mod}_{R}\to\mathbf{Mod}_{R}
\]

\end_inset

from the category of 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-modules to itself, where the 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-module 
\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

 is assigned to the 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-module 
\begin_inset Formula $M\otimes_{R}N$
\end_inset

 and where the 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-linear map 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi\colon M\to M'$
\end_inset

 is assigned to the 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-linear map 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi\otimes1\colon M\otimes_{R}N\to M'\otimes_{R}N$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi\otimes1$
\end_inset

 is defined by
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
(\varphi\otimes1)(u\otimes v)=\varphi(u)\otimes v
\]

\end_inset

for all elementary tensors 
\begin_inset Formula $u\otimes v\in M\otimes_{R}N$
\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{prop}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{proof}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 We need to check that 
\begin_inset Formula $-\otimes_{R}N$
\end_inset

 preserves compositions and identities.
 We first check that it preserves compositions.
 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi\colon M\to M'$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi'\colon M'\to M''$
\end_inset

 be two 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-linear maps and let 
\begin_inset Formula $u\otimes v$
\end_inset

 be an elementary tensor in 
\begin_inset Formula $M\otimes_{R}N$
\end_inset

.
 Then
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
((\varphi'\otimes1)(\varphi\otimes1))(u\otimes v) & =(\varphi'\otimes1)((\varphi\otimes1)(u\otimes v))\\
 & =(\varphi'\otimes1)(\varphi(u)\otimes v)\\
 & =(\varphi'(\varphi(u))\otimes v\\
 & =(\varphi'\varphi)(u)\otimes v\\
 & =(\varphi'\varphi\otimes1)(u\otimes v).
\end{align*}

\end_inset

It follows that 
\begin_inset Formula $(\varphi'\otimes1)(\varphi\otimes1)=\varphi'\varphi\otimes1$
\end_inset

.
 Hence 
\begin_inset Formula $-\otimes_{R}N$
\end_inset

 preserves compositions.
 Next we check that 
\begin_inset Formula $-\otimes_{R}N$
\end_inset

 preserves identities.
 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

 be an 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-module and 
\begin_inset Formula $u\otimes v$
\end_inset

 be an elementary tensor in 
\begin_inset Formula $M\otimes_{R}N$
\end_inset

.
 Then we have
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
(1_{M}\otimes1)(u\otimes v) & =1_{M}(u)\otimes v\\
 & =u\otimes v\\
 & =1_{M\otimes_{R}N}(u\otimes v).
\end{align*}

\end_inset

It follows that 
\begin_inset Formula $1_{M}\otimes1=1_{M\otimes_{R}N}$
\end_inset

.
 Hence 
\begin_inset Formula $-\otimes_{R}N$
\end_inset

 preserves identities.
 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{proof}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Right Exactness of 
\begin_inset Formula $-\otimes_{R}N$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{prop}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 The sequence of 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-modules and 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-linear maps
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{equation}
\backslash
label{covariantNtensorrightexact1}
\backslash
begin{tikzcd} M_1 
\backslash
arrow[r,"
\backslash
varphi _1 "] & M_2  
\backslash
arrow[r,"
\backslash
varphi _2 "] & M_3  
\backslash
arrow[r] & 0     
\backslash
end{tikzcd}
\backslash
end{equation}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
is exact if and only if for all 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-modules 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 the induced sequence 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{equation}
\backslash
label{covariantNtensorrightexact2}
\backslash
begin{tikzcd}  M_1 
\backslash
otimes _R N 
\backslash
arrow[r, " 
\backslash
varphi _1 
\backslash
otimes N "] & M_2 
\backslash
otimes _R N 
\backslash
arrow[r, " 
\backslash
varphi _2 
\backslash
otimes N "] & M_3 
\backslash
otimes _R N 
\backslash
arrow[r] & 0
\backslash
end{tikzcd}
\backslash
end{equation}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
is exact.
 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{prop}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{proof}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 The sequence 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{equation}
\backslash
label{covariantNtensorrightexact5}
\backslash
begin{tikzcd}  M_1 
\backslash
otimes _R N 
\backslash
arrow[r] & M_2 
\backslash
otimes _R N 
\backslash
arrow[r] & M_3 
\backslash
otimes _R N 
\backslash
arrow[r] & 0 
\backslash
end{tikzcd}
\backslash
end{equation}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 is exact for all 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-modules 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 if and only if for all 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-modules 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $P$
\end_inset

 the induced sequence
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
